<GlossaryTerm id="CDR0000322858"><TermName>laser surgery</TermName><TermPronunciation>(LAY-zer SER-juh-ree)</TermPronunciation><TermDefinition><DefinitionText>A surgical procedure that uses the cutting power of a laser beam to make bloodless cuts in tissue or to remove a surface lesion such as a tumor.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></TermDefinition><MediaLink ref="CDR0000711437" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;laser surgery&quot;" language="en" id="_3"/><MediaLink ref="CDR0000711436" type="audio/mpeg" alt="Pronunciation of dictionary term &quot;cirugía láser&quot;" language="es" id="_4"/><SpanishTermName>cirugía láser</SpanishTermName><SpanishTermDefinition><DefinitionText>Procedimiento quirúrgico que utiliza un rayo láser para hacer cortes sin derrame de sangre en el tejido o para extraer una lesión superficial; por ejemplo, un tumor.</DefinitionText><Dictionary>Cancer.gov</Dictionary><Audience>Patient</Audience></SpanishTermDefinition><DateFirstPublished>2003-07-26</DateFirstPublished><RelatedInformation><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="en" xref="http://www.cancer.gov/about-cancer/treatment/types/surgery/lasers-fact-sheet">Lasers in Cancer Treatment</RelatedExternalRef><RelatedExternalRef UseWith="es" xref="http://www.cancer.gov/espanol/cancer/tratamiento/tipos/cirugia/hoja-informativa-terapia-laser">Terapia láser para el tratamiento del cáncer</RelatedExternalRef></RelatedInformation></GlossaryTerm>
